	<h2>Additional Form Styling</h2>

	<h3>Errors</h3>
	<p>To draw attention to a field add a <code>.error</code> class name on the <code>.form-field</code> div.</p>
	<p>An <code>.alert</code> div can be used for general form errors. h1 - h4 headings can be used (and all style the same way).</p>
	<div class="outline example">
		<form>
			<div class="alert"><h1>There was an error.</h1>This is a general form alert wich shows as an error. Same as alert-error, or alert-formerror.</div>
			<div class="alert-warn"><h1>Class name alert-warn</h1>A message to consider.</div>
			<div class="alert-ok"><h1>Class name alert-ok</h1>A message of success or confirmation.</div>
			<div class="alert-info"><h1>Class name alert-info</h1>Any generic message.</div>
			<div class="alert-message"><h1>Class name alert-message</h1>Temporary use for feedback messages until notifications are introduced.</div>
			<fieldset>
				<legend>Legend</legend>
				<div class="form-field error">
					<label for="text1">Label name</label>
					<input type="text" id="text1" placeholder="Type something…">
					<span data-validation-for="text1">Example block-level help in a span.</span>
				</div>
			</fieldset>
		</form>
	</div>
